<item>
            <title>[LU-16947] Make multiop_bg_pause send the kill signal to the correct pid </title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-16947</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;multiop_bg_pause under test-framework starts multiop in background and waits for signal if &quot;_&quot; option is provided. On &apos;verbose&apos; mode the PAUSING string is printed on console which is checked and if not found error is reported by multiop_bg_pause function.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;On error, it is required to kill the existing running multiop binary as if not done will eventually timeout and not exit the test. Currently on error multiop_bg_pause function incorrectly sends singlal to wrong PID.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
